# Agent Flux — Cursor rules

## Monorepo
- `frontend/` — Next.js 15 (App Router). Client-side privacy, boundary review, trace UI.
- `backend/` — FastAPI Flux Cycle orchestrator (SSE). Never receives raw PII.
- `framework-docs/` — public methodology canon. Do not rewrite unless asked.
- `local/` — private hackathon docs (gitignored). Do not commit or edit unless asked.

## Privacy boundary (non-negotiable)
- Raw client text, PDF extraction, pseudonymization, and re-identification happen **only in the browser**.
- Backend receives **masked text** after human approval at boundary review.
- PRD exports re-identify locally via the mapping table; server-side output keeps placeholders.

## Gemma on-device
- Gemma 3 runs in the browser via MediaPipe + WebGPU (`frontend/lib/privacy/`).
- Default model path: `frontend/public/models/gemma3-270m-it-q4_0-web.task` (gitignored weights).
- Regex is the baseline; Gemma enriches NER when loaded. Fall back to regex on failure.
- Do not move pseudonymization to the backend or cloud APIs.

## Flux Cycle
- Backend pipeline: Plan → Retrieve → Tools → Escalation/Precedent → Critic → PRD (SSE trace).
- Escalation pauses the cycle; precedent skips repeat escalations in-session.
- Deterministic tools must remain testable without Vultr.

## Conventions
- Conventional Commits. Small, reviewable commits by work unit.
- Match existing patterns; minimal diffs. Tests with behavior changes.
- Run: `frontend` → `pnpm test`; `backend` → `uv run pytest`.
